      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(exec): remove misleading policy claim from approval prompt (#97069)",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes P2 issue #97069: When an exec command includes shell redirection (e.g., `openclaw --version 2>&1`), Allow Always is unavailable because the command is **non-persistable** (one-shot). However, the approval prompt incorrectly says:\n\n> \"The effective approval policy requires approval every time, so Allow Always is unavailable.\"\n\nThis is misleading even when the effective gateway exec policy is `security=allowlist` and `ask=on-miss`.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\n`buildApprovalPendingMessage` always assumed `allow-always` exclusion meant `ask === \"always\"`. But `allow-always` can also be excluded for non-persistable commands. Replaced the misleading message with a neutral one.\n\n## User Impact\n\nUsers running redirected commands see an accurate message. Plain commands continue to offer Allow Always normally.\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Real behavior proof (`npx tsx scripts/proof-issue-97069.ts`)\n\n```\nTEST 2: Redirected command — Allow Always NOT available\n\nCommand:     openclaw --version 2>&1\nDecisions:   allow-once, deny (no allow-always)\n\nBEFORE FIX:\n  \"The effective approval policy requires approval every time,\n   so Allow Always is unavailable.\"\n  → Misleading: user thinks policy is ask=always\n\nAFTER FIX:\n  \"Allow Always is unavailable for this command.\"\n  → Accurate: doesn't blame the policy\n\nContains old message: NO (correct) ✓\nContains new message: YES (correct) ✓\n```\n\n- `git diff --check` passed\n- 1 line changed in `src/agents/bash-tools.exec-runtime.ts`\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
        "branch": "fix/p2-issue-97069-approval-message",
